The paper deals with the layout of graphs in three-dimensional space, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). It also involves the colouring of vertices and edges, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.GT). The manipulation of track layouts involves algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), and the relationship between track layouts and other models of graph layout involves the study of graph representations (cs.SI).
